We referred to this link for different implementation tricks : https://jmetzen.github.io/2015-11-27/vae.html

Description of files :

mnist_data.py : Downloads the data from Yann LeCunn's website and does some preprocessing (extracts the data, labels, randomly shuffles the data)
vae.py : implementation of Variational AutoEncoder
run_main.py : main function which puts everything together
plot_utils.py: Plotting the reconstructed images and tsne representations

To run the code :

python run_main.py --dim_z 10 --num_epochs 100
